- For Trump, everything is a
masculinity contest as when he

00:04:51.550 --> 00:04:55.720
treated that his nuclear
button was much bigger and more

00:04:55.720 --> 00:04:59.730
powerful than Kim Jong Un's.

00:04:59.730 --> 00:05:01.840
Are we talking about buttons?

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:03.930
I don't think so.

00:05:03.930 --> 00:05:08.280
Trump's truculence reflects
what social psychologists

00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:13.080
call precarious masculinity,
the sense that manhood is not

00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:16.620
a biological inevitability,
but something that

00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:21.960
has to be earned over, and over,
and over again, and that it's

00:05:21.960 --> 00:05:24.010
a zero sum game.

00:05:24.010 --> 00:05:29.030
So one man's is
the biggest around.

00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:32.360
In the US, this
anxious masculinity

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:36.200
proved reassuring, particularly
in the face of the, quote,

00:05:36.200 --> 00:05:41.300
witch as the alt-right
referred to Hillary Clinton.

00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:45.380
The witch, of course,
is the deadly stereotype

00:05:45.380 --> 00:05:49.670
that justified the murder
of over 10,000 women

00:05:49.670 --> 00:05:54.240
in early modern Europe, many
of them targeted because they

00:05:54.240 --> 00:05:56.540
were widows with property.

00:05:56.540 --> 00:06:00.770
And so were seen of subversive
as then of the natural gender

00:06:00.770 --> 00:06:03.310
hierarchy.

00:06:03.310 --> 00:06:07.310
But the interesting
issue is not Trump,

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:11.600
it's the otherwise sensible
people who voted for him.

00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:14.390
We voted with our
middle finger, said one

00:06:14.390 --> 00:06:17.400
Trump, South Carolina voter.

00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:21.880
Trump's election
represented a collapse

00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:25.870
of the Democratic Party among
the white working class,

00:06:25.870 --> 00:06:28.070
especially men.

00:06:28.070 --> 00:06:31.250
And that's why four
crucial Rust Belt

00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:36.310
states swung the 2016 election.

00:06:36.310 --> 00:06:38.290
We've all heard a
lot about the divide

00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:43.000
between the 1% and the
99%, but the divide

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:47.935
that's driving
American politics today

00:06:47.935 --> 00:06:53.080
is a divide between the
professional managerial elite,

00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:58.520
the top 17%, and
middle class Americans,

00:06:58.520 --> 00:07:01.090
often called the
white working class.

00:07:01.090 --> 00:07:02.740
They're really the middle 53%.

00:07:06.230 --> 00:07:09.050
What are they so angry about?

00:07:09.050 --> 00:07:11.690
Well, really, two things.

00:07:11.690 --> 00:07:14.380
This slide shows the first.

00:07:14.380 --> 00:07:19.650
It's the demise of
the American dream.

00:07:19.650 --> 00:07:23.100
Virtually all Americans
born in the 1940s

00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:25.550
did better than their parents.

00:07:25.550 --> 00:07:28.070
But today, it's less than half.

00:07:31.830 --> 00:07:36.690
And class has been etched
into American geography, which

00:07:36.690 --> 00:07:43.500
explains that ocean of red in
rural and Rust Belt America.

00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:46.840
Here's the 2016 election map.

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:52.270
And you see the Democrats have
really become a regional party.

00:07:52.270 --> 00:07:56.440
The second reason why the
white working class is angry

00:07:56.440 --> 00:07:58.450
is cultural.

00:07:58.450 --> 00:08:00.430
They feel disrespected.

00:08:00.430 --> 00:08:02.410
And for a very simple reason.

00:08:02.410 --> 00:08:04.360
They are.

00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:08.950
After 1970s, elites
stopped connecting

00:08:08.950 --> 00:08:12.070
with Americans whom
prior generations gave

00:08:12.070 --> 00:08:15.290
a place of honor.

00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:22.160
So here is the Coit Tower
murals painted in the 1930s.

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:25.940
And you see how they celebrate
the nobility of blue collar

00:08:25.940 --> 00:08:27.880
work.

00:08:27.880 --> 00:08:34.270
That was on the wane by 1970s
when Blue collar Archie Bunker,

00:08:34.270 --> 00:08:37.809
of All in the Family,
was depicted as racist,

00:08:37.809 --> 00:08:41.919
and sexist, stupid, and fat.

00:08:41.919 --> 00:08:45.880
Then came Homer
Simpson in the 1990s

00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:50.440
who was amiable, but
also stupid and fat.

00:08:50.440 --> 00:08:52.540
And bringing it up
to the present day,

00:08:52.540 --> 00:08:56.530
think of Pennsatucky in
Orange is the New Black, who

00:08:56.530 --> 00:08:59.890
was depicted as a white,
working class woman,

00:08:59.890 --> 00:09:05.160
and we were invited to
laugh at her bad teeth.

00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:08.550
I enjoyed all three of
these shows, actually,

00:09:08.550 --> 00:09:13.320
but this kind of thing
has played into the hands

00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:15.810
of the far right.

00:09:15.810 --> 00:09:21.120
The alt-right also traffics
in precarious masculinity.

00:09:21.120 --> 00:09:23.730
They attack traditional
conservatives

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:28.860
as, quote, cucks, men who
raised the children of men

00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:31.760
who have cuckolded them.

00:09:31.760 --> 00:09:36.140
Traditional conservatives
respond in kind,

00:09:36.140 --> 00:09:39.530
insulting the
alt-right as, quote,

00:09:39.530 --> 00:09:44.828
childless single men
who masturbate to anime.

00:09:44.828 --> 00:09:48.670
The alt-right is
not blue collar.

00:09:48.670 --> 00:09:51.850
Richard Spencer describes
the classic member

00:09:51.850 --> 00:09:56.410
of his movement as someone
who, quote, is 30 years old,

00:09:56.410 --> 00:10:00.340
who is a tech professional,
who is an atheist,

00:10:00.340 --> 00:10:03.520
and who lives on
one of the coasts.

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:06.820
Greg Johnson, another
alt-right leader

00:10:06.820 --> 00:10:10.450
commented the alt-right
is drawing a higher

00:10:10.450 --> 00:10:14.080
caliber of people than
earlier iterations

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:17.830
of American white nationalism
because the career

00:10:17.830 --> 00:10:22.960
prospects of college educated
whites have declined.

00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:25.300
And a growing number
of young whites

00:10:25.300 --> 00:10:29.560
are returning home to live
with their parents, remaining

00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:34.290
unemployed or underemployed
for a long time.

00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:37.640
And their resentment grows.

00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:43.830
Again, the theme, whether
white collar or blue collar,

00:10:43.830 --> 00:10:46.640
there's nothing quite
so dangerous as a man

00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:49.610
without a future.

00:10:49.610 --> 00:10:55.670
We see this when suicide becomes
a career track for terrorists.

00:10:55.670 --> 00:11:01.040
We see it in the rise of
neo-nazis and anti-semites

00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:03.500
at home.

00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:06.780
The alt-right is openly racist.

00:11:06.780 --> 00:11:11.980
Their goal is a White ethnostate
without people of color,

00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:15.340
whether they were
born here or not.

00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:20.220
The question is how we can
peel of the economic anger

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:20.890
from the racism.

