You'll bear with me.

00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:16.180
One of the things that I
think we have to focus on--

00:12:16.180 --> 00:12:18.230
well, I'm just going to read it.

00:12:18.230 --> 00:12:19.820
You'll do the math.

00:12:19.820 --> 00:12:22.350
I suggest three steps.

00:12:22.350 --> 00:12:26.540
One is to provide a middle
class standard of living instead

00:12:26.540 --> 00:12:31.340
of our economy, in which we
have rich jobs for an ever

00:12:31.340 --> 00:12:35.300
decreasing portion
of the high elite

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:39.620
and muck jobs for everyone else.

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:43.810
The second is we need to
stop insulting people.

00:12:43.810 --> 00:12:46.300
We need to respect
people in blue collar

00:12:46.300 --> 00:12:48.760
jobs for simple reasons.

00:12:48.760 --> 00:12:50.860
They're human beings.

00:12:50.860 --> 00:12:53.650
We are committed
to social equality.

00:12:53.650 --> 00:12:56.830
And they do important work.

00:12:56.830 --> 00:13:01.030
When you turn on the tap in the
morning to brush your teeth,

00:13:01.030 --> 00:13:06.990
they're the reason water comes
out, not some Harvard grad.

00:13:06.990 --> 00:13:12.780
The third and most painful, we
need to reassess our attitudes

00:13:12.780 --> 00:13:15.250
towards immigration.

00:13:15.250 --> 00:13:19.870
Today, progressives typically
use an empathetic human rights

00:13:19.870 --> 00:13:26.030
lens for immigrants and
a judgmental neo-liberal,

00:13:26.030 --> 00:13:29.690
the race goes to the
swift, and you're not it,

00:13:29.690 --> 00:13:33.680
lens for the white
working class.

00:13:33.680 --> 00:13:37.110
And this is part of
a deeper dynamic.

00:13:37.110 --> 00:13:43.830
Today, elites in both
Europe and the United States

00:13:43.830 --> 00:13:48.480
display their cosmopolitanism
as a class act,

00:13:48.480 --> 00:13:52.780
a way of enacting
elite class status.

00:13:52.780 --> 00:13:56.430
We're cosmopolitan because
we went to college, where

00:13:56.430 --> 00:13:58.440
we formed global networks.

00:13:58.440 --> 00:14:01.440
And our job markets are global.

00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:04.470
That's just not true
of middle class people.

00:14:04.470 --> 00:14:07.800
It's not true of any non-elites.

00:14:07.800 --> 00:14:10.500
Their networks are very local.

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:12.240
They're very rooted.

00:14:12.240 --> 00:14:16.950
They're much more focused than
we are on community rather than

00:14:16.950 --> 00:14:20.250
just individual achievement.

00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:24.760
And you know, everyone tends
to stress the high status

00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:28.650
social categories
they belong to.

00:14:28.650 --> 00:14:32.190
That's why we cherish
our classiness

00:14:32.190 --> 00:14:36.400
by displaying cosmopolitanism.

00:14:36.400 --> 00:14:38.990
Middle class Americans,
on the other hand,

00:14:38.990 --> 00:14:42.460
are very proud of
being Americans.

00:14:42.460 --> 00:14:47.140
After all, that's one of the
only high status categories

00:14:47.140 --> 00:14:48.982
they belong to.

00:14:48.982 --> 00:14:55.860
To them, talk of open borders
shows a shocking and hurtful

00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:59.550
lack of social solidarity.

00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:03.810
And that's true of the
women as well as of the men.

00:15:03.810 --> 00:15:08.340
Many people are shocked that
white working class women

00:15:08.340 --> 00:15:11.430
went so heavily for Trump.

00:15:11.430 --> 00:15:14.040
White women without
college degrees

00:15:14.040 --> 00:15:17.970
voted for Trump by
a 38 point margin.

00:15:17.970 --> 00:15:24.080
If they had just split 50/50,
Clinton would have won.

00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:27.950
I wasn't surprised they didn't
vote for Clinton, although I

00:15:27.950 --> 00:15:33.190
voted for her and worked
endlessly for her.

00:15:33.190 --> 00:15:38.320
First, she failed to connect
with them because of her focus

00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:40.540
on the glass ceiling.

00:15:40.540 --> 00:15:43.300
When you think about
it, the glass ceiling

00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:46.300
is the metaphor that
stands for my right

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:50.320
to have as good a job
as my elite father.

00:15:50.320 --> 00:15:52.000
Why do they care?

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:53.930
They don't.

00:15:53.930 --> 00:15:57.560
Meanwhile, she was handed
on a silver platter

00:15:57.560 --> 00:16:01.460
sexual harassment through
the Access Hollywood tapes.

00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:07.250
That is an equal opportunity
gender disadvantage.

00:16:07.250 --> 00:16:09.210
She completely ignored it.

00:16:13.430 --> 00:16:21.230
So the reason that it is is
that, even if Clinton wasn't so

00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:25.550
class clueless, she
was running uphill

00:16:25.550 --> 00:16:29.870
because women in
blue collar families

00:16:29.870 --> 00:16:35.180
suffer the same dignitary
affronts as same class men.

00:16:35.180 --> 00:16:38.510
They have the same pride
in being Americans.

00:16:38.510 --> 00:16:42.350
They have the same
sense of violation

00:16:42.350 --> 00:16:47.660
when that pride is written
off as mere racism.

00:16:47.660 --> 00:16:52.570
Not to say that it's not
mixed often with racism,

00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:54.670
but that's a different
issue from whether it

00:16:54.670 --> 00:16:56.425
is only mere racism.

00:16:59.590 --> 00:17:05.810
And blue collar women feel the
same loss of blue collar jobs.

00:17:05.810 --> 00:17:09.280
And they feel it as
acutely as their men.

00:17:09.280 --> 00:17:13.089
Because the level of sex
segregation is sharply

00:17:13.089 --> 00:17:15.630
decreased for the likes of us.

00:17:15.630 --> 00:17:19.520
It's sharply decreased
among professionals.

00:17:19.520 --> 00:17:26.089
But it's decreased very little
in the working class contexts.

00:17:26.089 --> 00:17:29.470
And so they work
pink collar jobs.

00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:34.630
Have you ever tried to raise
a family on a pink collar job?

00:17:34.630 --> 00:17:36.130
Not easy.

00:17:36.130 --> 00:17:40.850
And that's what these women
in blue collar families say.

00:17:40.850 --> 00:17:44.260
Quote, I voted for
my boyfriend's job,

00:17:44.260 --> 00:17:48.280
said one Michigan Trump voter.

00:17:48.280 --> 00:17:52.060
The assumption that women would
vote for Clinton to help her

00:17:52.060 --> 00:17:56.500
break the glass ceiling,
a supreme example

00:17:56.500 --> 00:17:59.980
of class cluelessness.

00:17:59.980 --> 00:18:03.475
I don't know all the answers,
but I know one thing for sure.

00:18:06.470 --> 00:18:09.860
We do need to end
class cluelessness.

00:18:09.860 --> 00:18:12.260
It doesn't help immigrants.

00:18:12.260 --> 00:18:15.050
It doesn't help the
people of color.

00:18:15.050 --> 00:18:19.590
It doesn't help women
or the environment.

00:18:19.590 --> 00:18:23.127
The only thing it
helps is the far right.

00:18:23.127 --> 00:18:24.588
Thank you.

