up in knots the tolerance

01:25:39.140 --> 01:25:40.241
everybody, of everything.

01:25:40.241 --> 01:25:41.990
And that's where the
hate speech comes in.

01:25:41.990 --> 01:25:43.760
That's where the values come in.

01:25:43.760 --> 01:25:48.250
Does not have to be accepted
within a multi-ethnic society?

01:25:48.250 --> 01:25:52.110
Can a multi-ethnic society
exist by accepting everything?

01:25:52.110 --> 01:25:55.920
What that does is then just
become nothing and chaos.

01:25:55.920 --> 01:25:59.260
So what is the
prescriptive ideal?

01:25:59.260 --> 01:25:59.760
- Thank you.

01:25:59.760 --> 01:26:02.340
Please.

01:26:02.340 --> 01:26:04.780
- Thanks again for the question.

01:26:04.780 --> 01:26:08.970
I think that many of us indeed
gave a rather dark picture

01:26:08.970 --> 01:26:11.100
this afternoon.

01:26:11.100 --> 01:26:13.530
And the terms of civic
and ethnic nationalism

01:26:13.530 --> 01:26:16.350
are very helpful to describe it.

01:26:16.350 --> 01:26:18.690
Because in the many
countries we are discussing

01:26:18.690 --> 01:26:20.520
and we are
researching, there is,

01:26:20.520 --> 01:26:23.250
I think, a shift from
the civic to the ethnic.

01:26:23.250 --> 01:26:24.750
And that's not only
true in the US,

01:26:24.750 --> 01:26:27.240
but it's also true in
France, which you might see,

01:26:27.240 --> 01:26:29.310
it very specific,
but it becomes also

01:26:29.310 --> 01:26:32.100
very much defined
and very specific

01:26:32.100 --> 01:26:36.122
values that are, of course,
propagated as universal.

01:26:36.122 --> 01:26:37.830
But at the same time,
as you've described

01:26:37.830 --> 01:26:39.790
very nicely this
morning in the session,

01:26:39.790 --> 01:26:41.400
they are highly
specific, and also

01:26:41.400 --> 01:26:42.680
exclusionary towards others.

01:26:42.680 --> 01:26:46.410
So this is broader tendency
from specific to ethnic.

01:26:46.410 --> 01:26:48.060
That's all that we want.

01:26:48.060 --> 01:26:51.390
At the same time, my [INAUDIBLE]
to the slightly more ambivalent

01:26:51.390 --> 01:26:54.000
because it is also about
the rise and the embrace

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:55.494
of progressive values.

01:26:55.494 --> 01:26:56.910
And in the earlier
days, you would

01:26:56.910 --> 01:26:59.760
expect that being progressive
and being tolerant

01:26:59.760 --> 01:27:00.856
would go together.

01:27:00.856 --> 01:27:02.730
The problem is that,
also, progressive people

01:27:02.730 --> 01:27:05.165
can be highly intolerant.

01:27:05.165 --> 01:27:06.540
But I do see, in
the Netherlands,

01:27:06.540 --> 01:27:07.820
it has a performative effect.

01:27:07.820 --> 01:27:10.110
So all the time
emphasizing women's rights,

01:27:10.110 --> 01:27:14.220
and other, and LGBT rights
creates something like--

01:27:14.220 --> 01:27:16.710
OK, but then we should be
tolerant towards minorities,

01:27:16.710 --> 01:27:20.280
groups in a disqualified, in
a discriminated situation.

01:27:20.280 --> 01:27:24.750
So why then not having the
embracement of the notion

01:27:24.750 --> 01:27:26.630
of tolerance itself?

01:27:26.630 --> 01:27:30.750
And not just for those specific
groups, but we should rethink.

01:27:30.750 --> 01:27:32.520
And that gets closer
to, of course,

01:27:32.520 --> 01:27:36.120
then the civic notion
that is not relativistic.

01:27:36.120 --> 01:27:39.110
To be totally clear, I
totally agree with you there.

01:27:39.110 --> 01:27:41.970
But that is far from
saying, some people

01:27:41.970 --> 01:27:44.550
are, by color, or by
birth, or whatever,

01:27:44.550 --> 01:27:46.860
more core of the
nation than others.

01:27:46.860 --> 01:27:51.360
Everybody can become
part of that nation.

01:27:51.360 --> 01:27:56.580
- Does anybody have a model
nation we can look to?

01:27:56.580 --> 01:27:59.660
- I try to avoid that.

01:27:59.660 --> 01:28:02.100
There is not such
a country, I guess.

01:28:02.100 --> 01:28:04.060
- You say what?

01:28:04.060 --> 01:28:06.050
- I'm curious to hear
from the audience,

01:28:06.050 --> 01:28:10.530
but I mean, they are clearly
hesitant to name countries that

01:28:10.530 --> 01:28:13.970
are closer to this ideal
of civic nationalism.

01:28:13.970 --> 01:28:17.670
What we do see is that many go
from civic to ethnic or a sense

01:28:17.670 --> 01:28:18.340
of nationalism.

01:28:18.340 --> 01:28:19.860
But there are good examples.

01:28:19.860 --> 01:28:21.360
You can think of
countries that have

01:28:21.360 --> 01:28:23.790
become more civic recently.

01:28:23.790 --> 01:28:26.300
I'm afraid that's very
hard to come up with.

01:28:26.300 --> 01:28:30.360
- Let me just add that ethnic,
of course, you can touch,

01:28:30.360 --> 01:28:33.300
you know, you can see
to a certain degree.

01:28:33.300 --> 01:28:35.880
Civic is an abstract notion.

01:28:35.880 --> 01:28:39.300
Modernity's main problem
is that the notions,

01:28:39.300 --> 01:28:43.080
the concepts we have, have a
certain level of abstraction.

01:28:43.080 --> 01:28:46.020
You cannot find
them actually there.

01:28:46.020 --> 01:28:49.500
And I'm now very upset
about this imagined part

01:28:49.500 --> 01:28:53.310
of the imagined community
that nationalism entails.

01:28:53.310 --> 01:28:56.220
Because when you say
imagined, everybody

01:28:56.220 --> 01:28:57.720
imagines it differently.

01:28:57.720 --> 01:29:01.170
So what happens if those
imaginations don't all go

01:29:01.170 --> 01:29:01.890
along?

01:29:01.890 --> 01:29:06.570
And how do you take that theory
and what happens in practice?

01:29:06.570 --> 01:29:08.310
There is a lot of variation.

01:29:08.310 --> 01:29:13.200
The only insight I have
is [INAUDIBLE] insight.

01:29:13.200 --> 01:29:16.830
I think if we have
as individuals

01:29:16.830 --> 01:29:19.740
the unit of analysis, it's
going to be difficult.

01:29:19.740 --> 01:29:22.240
We have to think
of communal again.

01:29:22.240 --> 01:29:25.200
Maybe that is the way to
go, of communal rights

01:29:25.200 --> 01:29:26.234
and responsibilities.

01:29:26.234 --> 01:29:27.900
- I'm eager to hear
the other questions.

01:29:27.900 --> 01:29:30.270
But let me just say
one brief thing.

01:29:30.270 --> 01:29:34.290
This is not the first time
we've seen this movie, folks.

01:29:34.290 --> 01:29:37.710
I mean, my mother was Jewish.

01:29:37.710 --> 01:29:40.880
She wasn't considered American.

01:29:40.880 --> 01:29:43.470
I'm married to a Catholic boy.

01:29:43.470 --> 01:29:46.500
There was a time when
the Catholics and Irish

01:29:46.500 --> 01:29:48.540
were considered black.

01:29:48.540 --> 01:29:53.010
We have done this our
whole national lives.

01:29:53.010 --> 01:29:54.480
We can do it again.

01:29:54.480 --> 01:29:56.400
We just need to want to.

01:29:56.400 --> 01:29:57.810
And we just need--

01:29:57.810 --> 01:30:00.360
and I would never--

01:30:00.360 --> 01:30:03.000
